  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And then we were transferred to Latvia.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And there we had a-- we were right in a battle where-- between-- because in Latvia, in Courland, was a section where, where there were Vlasov-- see, their Russian, Russian General Vlasov, who had-- he was the Ukrainian who went, actually, in helping the Germans.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he created the army who was loyal to the Germans and fought on behalf of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And they were actually-- part of this army was surrounded in Courland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And there were going on very, very strong battles.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And one of those, when I was with my officer, which-- I used to translate for him-- we were shelled.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And they have actually shelled our jeep-- fell a, a, a shell and exploded.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And the officer and the, the other guy that was with me-- the only guy that was saved from this happening was myself.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I was-- I lost, actually, my-- I, I was-- lost, actually, my-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I, I was not able to recover.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "At least, for-- when I recovered, I find myself in the hospital.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Fortunately, nothing serious happened to me, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And I was back on the-- I lost my consciousness at the time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And I was back, back at the-- with the-- with the-- with the army.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "As time went by, we have-- and then the developments-- military-- went very well for the Russians.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I mean, the, the army was-- just finished liberating most of Lithuania, and Latvia, and also Courland.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And those, those parts-- those pockets of resistance were actually completely eliminated.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Then suddenly, on the-- on the other front with Japan, happened something very strange.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
